==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tribulation
<hw>Trib`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tribulacium</ets>, F. <ets>tribulation</ets>, L.
<ets>tribulatio</ets>, from <ets>tribulare</ets> to press, afflict, fr.
<ets>tribulum</ets> a thrashing sledge, akin to <ets>terere</ets>,
<ets>tritum</ets>, to rub. See <er>Trite</er>.]</ety> <def>That which
occasions distress, trouble, or vexation; severe affliction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When <qex>tribulation</qex> or persecution ariseth because of the
word, by and by he is offended.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xiii.
21.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the world ye shall have <qex>tribulation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>John. xvi. 33.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tribunal</ent>⟦br⟧
